trans-unit.source: Provides a user interface for a <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.Design.WindowsFormsComponentEditor"></xref>.
A ComponentEditorForm shows a view of available component editor pages along with a user interface for selection.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.Design.ComponentEditorForm"></xref> class.
The component to be edited.
The set of <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.Design.ComponentEditorPage"></xref> objects to be shown in the form.

<xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if the form will automatically resize; <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref> if it must be manually resized.
Occurs when the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Form.AutoSize*> property changes.
To be added.
Raises the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.Form.Activated"></xref> event.
The first time the OnActivated method is executed, it shows the first component editor page in the list.
Raising an event invokes the event handler through a delegate.
For more information, see [Events](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).
The OnActivated method also allows derived classes to handle the event without attaching a delegate.
This is the preferred technique for handling the event in a derived class.
An <xref:System.EventArgs> that contains the event data.
Raises the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.Control.HelpRequested"></xref> event.
The OnHelpRequested method shows the Help page that is associated with the component editor page, if there is one.
Raising an event invokes the event handler through a delegate.
For more information, see [Events](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).
The OnHelpRequested method also allows derived classes to handle the event without attaching a delegate.
This is the preferred technique for handling the event in a derived class.
